# Basics-of-Programming-Java-Programming


Number of characters excluding space
easy
Time Limit: 2 sec
Memory Limit: 128000 kB
Problem Statement
Given a string s, Find total number of characters excluding spaces.
Input
First line of the input contains the string s.

Constraints
1 <= s. size() <= 105
Output
Print number of characters excluding space
Example
Sample Input 1:
newton School

Sample Output 1:
12

////////////////////**********************//////////////////////////////



import java.io.*; // for handling input/output
import java.util.*; // contains Collections framework

// don't change the name of this class
// you can add inner classes if needed
class Main {
    public static void main (String[] args) {
                      // Your code here
                      int sum=0;
        Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
        String val=s.nextLine();
        int len=val.length();
            for(int i=0;i<len;i++)
            {
                if(val.charAt(i)==' ')
                    {
                        continue;
                    }
                    sum++;
            }
                    System.out.println(sum);
        }
}
